name: dynamin GTPase
classes: Acting on GTP to facilitate cellular and subcellular movement
comment: An enzyme with a molecular mass of about 100 kDa that is involved in endocytosis and is instrumental in pinching off membrane vesicles.

references.title: Dynamin GTPase, a force-generating molecular switch.
Dynamin at the neck of caveolae mediates their budding to form transport vesicles by GTP-driven fission from the plasma membrane of endothelium.
